import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['people'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by year?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('age')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['age'], data['people'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sex_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(sex_counts, labels=sex_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people by sex?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.pivot_table(index='age', columns='year', values='people')
    ax = sns.heatmap(data, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt='d', linewidths=.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Age')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of people by age and year?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['year'], data['people'], width=365, align='center', alpha=0.5, color=['blue', 'red'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('People')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people by year and sex?')
    ax.legend(['Male', 'Female'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
